"1" = "Well, I must endure the presence of a few caterpillars if I wish to become acquainted with the butterflies.";
"2" = "The most beautiful things in the world cannot be seen or touched, they are felt with the heart.";
"3" = "It is the time you have wasted for your rose that makes your rose so important.";
"4" = "No one is ever satisfied where he is.";
"5" = "If you love a flower that lives on a star, it is sweet to look at the sky at night. All the stars are a-bloom with flowers...";
"6" = "It is such a mysterious place, the land of tears.";
"7" = "What makes the desert beautiful,' said the little prince, 'is that somewhere it hides a well...";
"8" = "To you I am nothing more than a fox like a hundred thousand other foxes. But if you tame me, then we shall need each other. To me, you will be unique in all the world. To you, I shall be unique in all the world.";

"9" = "I am who I am and I have the need to be.";
"10" = "To forget a friend is sad. Not everyone has had a friend.";
"11" = "In one of those stars I shall be living. In one of them I shall be laughing. And so it will be as if all the stars were laughing, when you look at the sky at night.";
"12" = "And when your sorrow is comforted (time soothes all sorrows) you will be content that you have known me. You will always be my friend...I shall not leave you.";
"13" = "The proof that the little prince existed is that he was charming, that he laughed, and that he was looking for a sheep. If anybody wants a sheep, that is a proof that he exists.";
"14" = "I remembered the fox. One runs the risk of crying a bit if one allows oneself to be tamed.";
"15" = "The only things you learn are the things you tame";
"16" = "You become responsible, forever, for what you have tamed.";
"17" = "You see, one loves the sunset when one is so sad.";
"18" = "It is much more difficult to judge oneself than to judge others.";
"19" = "What matters most are the simple pleasures so abundant that we can all enjoy them";
"20" = "A rock pile ceases to be a rock pile the moment a single man contemplates it, bearing within him the image of a cathedral.";
"21" = "And now here is my secret, a very simple secret: It is only with the heart that one can see rightly; what is essential is invisible to the eye.";
"22" = "Words are the source of misunderstandings.";
"23" = "All grown-ups were once children... but only few of them remember it.";
"24" ="I have lived a great deal among grown-ups. I have seen them intimately, close at hand. And that hasn’t much improved my opinion of them.";
"25" = "“The thing that is important is the thing that is not seen.”";
"26" = "I wonder,” he said, “whether the stars are set alight in heaven so that one day each one of us may find his own again...";
"27" = "Only the children know what they are looking for.";

